                        <h3>How it All Got Started</h3>
                        
                        <p class="mx-3">In 2018, two Georgian College students in the Social Service Worker programme, under the direction of the Centre for Changemaking and Social Innovation, proposed a Digital Food Map to address the issue of food waste and food insecurity in their community, Orillia. </p>
                        <p class="mx-3">
                            The next step was to develop an online application. The Centre for Changemaking, in partnership with The Sharing Place of Orillia, called upon students in Georgian's Interactive Media Design - Web programme to develop this application, now branded as "The FoodShare Map".
                        </p>
