                            <h3>Who We Serve</h3>    
                            <p class="mx-3">In 2017 the Commission for Environmental Cooperation issued a report on food waste in Canada. It found that 396 kilograms of food per capita is wasted when all stages of the food supply chain in Canada are considered.<sub><a href="#footnote-1">(1)</a></sub>  This represents 20 trillion kilocalories. At the same time, estimates are that 13% of Canadians go hungry — representing over four million men, women and children.<sub><a href="#footnote-2">(2) </a></sub> </p>
                            <p class="mx-3">Initally The FoodShare Map will focus on the community of Orillia, but in developing the application thought has been given to scaling up to include other communties. We welcome inquiries.</p>
                        </div>
