                                <h3 class="mt-4">Our Name and Logo</h3>

                                <p class="mx-3">The FoodShare Map logo includes a stylized map that is representative of map services found online. The type face used in the logo is Biko Regular. It is described by its author, Marco Ugolini, as a "geometric sans serif with a strong and yet friendly character". The name of the font is a tribute to Steve Biko <sub><a href="#footnote-3">(3) </a></sub>. Mr. Biko was a South African anti-apartheid activist who believed that community projects were a way to alleviate poverty and build better societies. Mr. Biko sets an example for us all and we continue to pay tribute to him by incorporating this type face into our logo.</p>


                                <p class="mx-3">The name "The FoodShare Map" represents a change in thinking when dealing with people who are food insecure. Foodbanks, once thought of as temporary measures for difficult times, have become fixtures in our communities. At the same time, a consciousness is growing that as a society we should not waste our abundant resources. </p>
                            
